When you write some text in a new file and you want to exit the editor, the Save button does not work. It only works if the file already exists. 2. If there is no space between a Python code and a comment, the comment is not highlighted correctly. 3. If auto indentation is enabled, the character(s) used for indentation should be the one(s) set in Indentation Character setting. I also have two suggestions: 1. Main and New/Open/Save menus could be merged to increase simplicity. 2. An option to see hidden characters wouldn't be bad either. ;)

Actual Rating: ~3.75 stars  So far I like the editor, it's got some great features with cloud syncing and the interface is nice to edit with. But I just found one problem when upgrading to the Pro version. The Pro is a COMPLETELY SEPARATE app! This means I'm having to resync everything and customize the settings again. An "upgrade" should just add a license/serial that removes the ads. This way my app is already setup from before and ready to use. How does this even become a legitimate business decision?  UPDATE: Feedback Two things  1st) The cursor auto-centering behavior is annoying and can be bothersome when trying to type, as it could center the cursor just above the keyboard, making it hard to adjust the cursor if needed. A possible solution to this would be allowing manual scrolling while the keyboard is in view, and scrolling past the end of the code.  2nd) The accessory keyboard/view should always be visible. Even when the normal keyboard is present. It should be nested on top of the keyboard.

Doesn't work with certain web hosts such as DreamHost.  Other applications that can access files via SFTP can handle scenarios where a web host exposes root folders that aren't fully accessible to users.  For example you can see that there is a home folder off the root, but you only have access to your own subfolder within the home folder.  If you navigate to the home folder it throws a java exception and doesn't display your subfolder for you to navigate to.  This means I have no way to even get into the folder that I have access to in order to access my files.  Until this bug is fixed, this software is useless to me.
